<subSubSection lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="18" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,984,1978]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,1333,1359]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body reddish brown, shining. Length of pronotum + elytra = 2.2–3.6 mm (males), 2.1–3.6 (females). Punctation of head fine and sparse, finer than pronotum. Pronotum widest near middle, sides obtusely rounded, basal angles obtuse; ratio length:width = 1:1.4; finely punctate with faint reticulate microsculpture. Elytra of medium length, wider than pronotum, ratio length:width = 1:0.7; stria 1 clearly impressed, remaining striae punctate, confused; interval punctures slightly smaller than strial punctures. Antennal club (
<figureCitation box="[333,419,1526,1552]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–35" captionStartId="17.[151,272,1147,1171]" captionTargetBox="[233,1357,204,1114]" captionTargetId="figure-282@17.[229,1357,197,1122]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 29–35. Hydnobius longidens. 29. Right antenna, dorsal view. 30. Mandibles, dorsal view. 31. Male right protibia. 32. Male right metafemur. 33. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 34. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 35. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Figs. 34, 35), 0.4 mm (Figs. 29, 30, 33), 0.5 mm (Figs. 31, 32)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310904/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) moderately broad, ratio club width:length = 1:2.7; width ratio of antennomeres 7:8:9 = 1.2:1:1.6. Mandibles (
<figureCitation box="[436,523,1565,1591]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–35" captionStartId="17.[151,272,1147,1171]" captionTargetBox="[233,1357,204,1114]" captionTargetId="figure-282@17.[229,1357,197,1122]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 29–35. Hydnobius longidens. 29. Right antenna, dorsal view. 30. Mandibles, dorsal view. 31. Male right protibia. 32. Male right metafemur. 33. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 34. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 35. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Figs. 34, 35), 0.4 mm (Figs. 29, 30, 33), 0.5 mm (Figs. 31, 32)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310904/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
) moderately elongate; right mandible bidentate apically, with a median tooth on inner margin; left mandible with a tooth on apical one-half of inner margin. Profemur and mesofemur of both sexes unarmed. Male metafemur (
<figureCitation box="[615,702,1642,1668]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–35" captionStartId="17.[151,272,1147,1171]" captionTargetBox="[233,1357,204,1114]" captionTargetId="figure-282@17.[229,1357,197,1122]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 29–35. Hydnobius longidens. 29. Right antenna, dorsal view. 30. Mandibles, dorsal view. 31. Male right protibia. 32. Male right metafemur. 33. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 34. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 35. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Figs. 34, 35), 0.4 mm (Figs. 29, 30, 33), 0.5 mm (Figs. 31, 32)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310904/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
) with a large tooth on posterior margin before apex; posterior margin basal to tooth may be irregularly serrulate; female metafemur unarmed. Both sexes with protibia widened apically; male protibial spur (
<figureCitation box="[628,718,1720,1746]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–35" captionStartId="17.[151,272,1147,1171]" captionTargetBox="[233,1357,204,1114]" captionTargetId="figure-282@17.[229,1357,197,1122]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 29–35. Hydnobius longidens. 29. Right antenna, dorsal view. 30. Mandibles, dorsal view. 31. Male right protibia. 32. Male right metafemur. 33. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 34. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 35. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Figs. 34, 35), 0.4 mm (Figs. 29, 30, 33), 0.5 mm (Figs. 31, 32)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310904/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
) broad; mesotibia and metatibia moderately broad in both sexes. All tibiae, in both sexes, spinose on outer margin. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[830,901,1758,1784]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Male.</emphasis>
Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1043,1129,1758,1784]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–35" captionStartId="17.[151,272,1147,1171]" captionTargetBox="[233,1357,204,1114]" captionTargetId="figure-282@17.[229,1357,197,1122]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 29–35. Hydnobius longidens. 29. Right antenna, dorsal view. 30. Mandibles, dorsal view. 31. Male right protibia. 32. Male right metafemur. 33. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 34. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 35. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Figs. 34, 35), 0.4 mm (Figs. 29, 30, 33), 0.5 mm (Figs. 31, 32)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310904/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
) with median lobe broad, narrowing to small rounded lobe at apex. Parameres sinuate, concave medially at apex, with two apical setae. Internal sac apically with curved rows of broad, flat setae, and basally with a pair of sclerotized oblong lobes; lobes visible when internal sac is inverted. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[660,758,1874,1900]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Female.</emphasis>
Coxites (
<figureCitation box="[873,959,1875,1901]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–35" captionStartId="17.[151,272,1147,1171]" captionTargetBox="[233,1357,204,1114]" captionTargetId="figure-282@17.[229,1357,197,1122]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 29–35. Hydnobius longidens. 29. Right antenna, dorsal view. 30. Mandibles, dorsal view. 31. Male right protibia. 32. Male right metafemur. 33. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 34. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 35. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Figs. 34, 35), 0.4 mm (Figs. 29, 30, 33), 0.5 mm (Figs. 31, 32)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310904/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
) elongate, cylindrical, with apical setae; styli minute, inserted at apices of coxites. Sternite 8 (
<figureCitation box="[801,890,1913,1939]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–35" captionStartId="17.[151,272,1147,1171]" captionTargetBox="[233,1357,204,1114]" captionTargetId="figure-282@17.[229,1357,197,1122]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 29–35. Hydnobius longidens. 29. Right antenna, dorsal view. 30. Mandibles, dorsal view. 31. Male right protibia. 32. Male right metafemur. 33. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 34. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 35. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Figs. 34, 35), 0.4 mm (Figs. 29, 30, 33), 0.5 mm (Figs. 31, 32)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310904/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
) rounded apically; anterior apophysis broad, weakly rounded apically.
</paragraph>
