<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1290,1858]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,466,1290,1316]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Nomenclatural notes.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Horn, G. H." box="[474,679,1290,1316]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="219 - 322" refId="ref29843" refString="Horn, G. H. (1880) Synopsis of the Silphidae of the United States with reference to the genera of other countries. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 8, 219 - 322." type="journal article" year="1880">Horn (1880: 281)</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName authority="LeConte" authorityName="LeConte" box="[773,1032,1290,1316]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Hydnobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longidens">
<emphasis box="[773,923,1291,1316]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">H. longidens</emphasis>
LeConte
</taxonomicName>
into synonymy under 
<taxonomicName authority="LeConte, 1879: 511" authorityName="LeConte" authorityPageNumber="511" authorityYear="1879" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Hydnobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longulus">
<emphasis box="[1299,1435,1291,1316]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">H. longulus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="LeConte, J. L." box="[151,393,1329,1355]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="499 - 520" refId="ref30129" refString="LeConte, J. L. (1879) The Coleoptera of the Alpine Rocky Mountain Regions. Part II. Bulletin of the United States Geological and Geographical Survey of the Territories, 5, 499 - 520." type="journal article" year="1879">LeConte, 1879: 511</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, LeConte described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1879" box="[765,905,1329,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Hydnobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longulus">
<emphasis box="[765,905,1329,1354]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">H. longulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from a mixed series which we recognize as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peck &amp; Cook" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="LeConte" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[151,313,1368,1393]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Sogda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusa">
<emphasis box="[151,313,1368,1393]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Sogda obtusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(LeConte’s “ 
<typeStatus box="[475,541,1368,1394]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Type</typeStatus>
”) and 
<taxonomicName box="[621,775,1368,1393]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Hydnobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longidens">
<emphasis box="[621,775,1368,1393]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">H. longidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(LeConte’s “ 
<typeStatus box="[936,998,1368,1394]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Type</typeStatus>
2”). Horn’s action did not solve the problem of application of names. We have resolved this situation by placing 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1879" box="[1044,1181,1407,1432]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Hydnobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longulus">
<emphasis box="[1044,1181,1407,1432]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">H. longulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into synonymy under 
<taxonomicName authority="(LeConte, 1879)" authorityName="Peck &amp; Cook" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="LeConte" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[151,516,1445,1471]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Sogda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusa">
<emphasis box="[151,310,1445,1470]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Sogda obtusa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="LeConte, J. L." box="[326,507,1445,1471]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="499 - 520" refId="ref30129" refString="LeConte, J. L. (1879) The Coleoptera of the Alpine Rocky Mountain Regions. Part II. Bulletin of the United States Geological and Geographical Survey of the Territories, 5, 499 - 520." type="journal article" year="1879">LeConte, 1879</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Our action of attaching names to actual specimens clarifies and stabilizes use of the names.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1290,1858]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,359,1522,1548]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Distribution.</emphasis>
